In this statement, the President of the United States commemorates the 22nd anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda. He expresses solidarity with the Rwandan people and remembers the over 800,000 lives lost during the 100 days of violence. The President honors not only the victims but also those who risked their lives to save others, as well as the survivors who carry the memories of the atrocities. He emphasizes the importance of recognizing our common humanity and shared commitment to protecting civilians and preventing mass atrocities. The President also acknowledges the progress made by Rwanda in moving beyond these crimes and building a more peaceful and prosperous future. The United States government and its people pledge to continue supporting Rwanda and reaffirm their commitment to protecting the vulnerable and upholding the dignity of every human being.